article_title: ‘You spelled mockery wrong’: @BarackObama claims interest in O-care is growing – twitchy.com
article_text:
@BarackObama, the Twitter account of Organizing for Action, wants everybody to assume that “interest” is something always generated by something positive:

A new report shows that interest in the @Obamacare marketplace continues to grow: http://t.co/FBKWzu67OO #GetCovered — Barack Obama (@BarackObama) November 6, 2013

Concerned citizens took to Twitter to help straighten out that statement:

Train wrecks are fascinating RT @BarackObama: A new report shows that interest in the @Obamacare marketplace continues to grow. — Will Antonin (@Will_Antonin) November 6, 2013

@CAAmyO It’s like being interested in a pile up on the highway. — Bill Murphy (@billmurphy) November 6, 2013

You spelled mockery wrong RT @BarackObama: A new report shows that interest in the @Obamacare marketplace continues to grow #GetCovered — Amy Lutz (@amylutz4) November 6, 2013

You confuse "interest in" with "mockery of." MT @BarackObama New report shows that interest in the @Obamacare marketplace continues to grow — jon gabriel (@exjon) November 6, 2013

People were interested in 2 girls 1 cup also RT @BarackObama: new report shows that interest in the @Obamacare marketplace continues to grow — Stephen Miller (@redsteeze) November 6, 2013

If anything, Obamacare has been a mockery stimulus the likes of which not even “Recovery Summer” could create.
